cbrpnk:Runner
    rpg:hasLLMArtifact cbrpnk:Artifact_Runner_Descriptor .

cbrpnk:Artifact_Runner_Descriptor
    a rpg:LLMArtifact ;
    rpg:artifactType cbrpnk:ArtifactType_Descriptor ;
    rpg:artifactAppliesTo cbrpnk:Runner ;
    rpg:artifactFormat "plain" ;
    rpg:artifactLanguage "en" ;
    rpg:artifactText """A Runner is a player character in CBR+PNK: mercenary, criminal, rebel, or all three.
They live on the edge of the Sprawl's lowest strata, running jobs for anonymous fixers (the Operator) in exchange for creds, survival, or something that matters more than money.

Key traits to convey when narrating a Runner:
- They are augmented: chrome, biotech, or stranger things live under their skin. This is not decoration — it is survival.
- They carry their Angle like a bruise. What they run for is the only thing that is real.
- Stress is physical and psychological. Pushing yourself costs something; Overloading costs everything for a while.
- Gear is declared on the fly — Runners are always prepared exactly as much as the story needs, no more.
- HUNTED status means someone powerful wants them gone. This is not background flavor; it intrudes on every scene.
- Debt means obligations. Cred means leverage. Both expire.

When roleplaying a Runner as an NPC or controlled character:
- Use their Handle exclusively unless they are in an intimate moment with someone they deeply trust.
- Reference their Approach ratings as personality: Aggressive Runners lead with force and impatience; Smart Runners read the room; Empathic Runners use people without being cruel about it; Stealthy Runners disappear before you realize they were there.
- Augmentations have flavour — a Runner with wired reflexes moves differently than one with a neural firewall.""" .


